abstract: Kuwait's oil minister said on Sunday he hoped Kuwait and Saudi Arabia will resolve the Neutral Zone issue by the end of 2019.
snippet: Kuwait's oil minister said on Sunday he hoped Kuwait and Saudi Arabia will resolve the Neutral Zone issue by the end of 2019.
lead_paragraph: KUWAIT — Kuwait's oil minister said on Sunday he hoped Kuwait and Saudi Arabia will resolve the Neutral Zone issue by the end of 2019.
headline_main: Kuwait Hopes to Resolve Neutral Zone Oil Issue With Saudi Arabia by Year End
headline_print_headline: Kuwait Hopes to Resolve Neutral Zone Oil Issue With Saudi Arabia by Year End

abstract: Prime Minister Narendra Modi stridently backed a law establishing a religious test for migrants that has led to deadly protests.
snippet: Prime Minister Narendra Modi stridently backed a law establishing a religious test for migrants that has led to deadly protests.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India delivered on Sunday a strident defense of a contentious citizenship law that has fueled deadly protests, accusing opposition politicians of “spreading lies” and demonstrators of trying to destroy the country through vandalism and bloodshed.

abstract: Impeachment is a big story. In the Impeachment Briefing newsletter, I pull out each day’s most important threads so you can follow along in a different way.
snippet: Impeachment is a big story. In the Impeachment Briefing newsletter, I pull out each day’s most important threads so you can follow along in a different way.
lead_paragraph: Times Insider explains who we are and what we do, and delivers behind-the-scenes insights into how our journalism comes together.

headline_main: On the Impeachment Beat, but in Your Inbox

abstract: The American-born Lady Astor was the first woman to take a seat in the British Parliament. A century later, her legacy is still being debated.
snippet: The American-born Lady Astor was the first woman to take a seat in the British Parliament. A century later, her legacy is still being debated.
lead_paragraph: PLYMOUTH, England — When women finally won the right in 1918 to enter Britain’s Parliament, many expected the first female lawmaker to sit there to come from the ranks of the suffragists, the activists who had fought, often at huge personal cost, for the vote.

abstract: Protesters angered by India's new citizenship law that excludes Muslims defied a ban against demonstrations on Sunday, as Prime Minister Narendra Modi used a rally for his Hindu nationalist party to defend the legislation, accusing the opposition of pushing the country into a “fear psychosis."

headline_main: India's Leader Defends New Law as Protests Against It Go On
headline_print_headline: India's Leader Defends New Law as Protests Against It Go On

abstract: All five parties running in a parliamentary election in Uzbekistan on Sunday have backed reformist President Shavkat Mirziyoyev, meaning that although the vote will be the freest in decades, it is likely to produce a legislature loyal to him.
snippet: All five parties running in a parliamentary election in Uzbekistan on Sunday have backed reformist President Shavkat Mirziyoyev, meaning that although the vote will be the freest in decades, it is likely to produce a legislature loyal to him.
lead_paragraph: ALMATY — All five parties running in a parliamentary election in Uzbekistan on Sunday have backed reformist President Shavkat Mirziyoyev, meaning that although the vote will be the freest in decades, it is likely to produce a legislature loyal to him.
headline_main: More Freedom, but Predictable Outcome: Uzbekistan Votes for New Parliament
headline_print_headline: More Freedom, but Predictable Outcome: Uzbekistan Votes for New Parliament

abstract: Afghan President Ashraf Ghani appears to have narrowly won a second term, according to preliminary results from September's balloting that were announced Sunday, although his main challenger rejected the outcome as illegitimate.
snippet: Afghan President Ashraf Ghani appears to have narrowly won a second term, according to preliminary results from September's balloting that were announced Sunday, although his main challenger rejected the outcome as illegitimate.
lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — Afghan President Ashraf Ghani appears to have narrowly won a second term, according to preliminary results from September's balloting that were announced Sunday, although his main challenger rejected the outcome as illegitimate.
headline_main: Afghan President Appears to Win New Term in Initial Results
headline_print_headline: Afghan President Appears to Win New Term in Initial Results

abstract: Afghanistan's incumbent President Ashraf Ghani won a slim majority of votes in a Sept. 28 election, delayed preliminary results showed on Sunday, after a poll that plunged the country into political crisis and was marred by allegations of fraud.
